articles.description: David Caraher scored 23 points, grabbed nine rebounds and passed for five assists as Houston Baptist roared back from a 17-point first-half deficit to keep Northwestern State winless in Southland Conference play, 77-70 on Wednesday night.
articles.headline: Houston Baptist roars back to beat Northwestern St, 77-70

articles.description: Tyler Hagedorn had 20 points and 10 rebounds and South Dakota opened the second half on a 31-8 run and beat Oral Roberts 85-67 on Wednesday night.
articles.headline: South Dakota jumps out in 2nd half, beats Oral Roberts 85-67

articles.description: Nick Garth scored 19 points and Lamar solidified its hold on a post-season tournament berth by thumping Incarnate Word, 85-62, on Wednesday night, keeping the Cardinals winless in Southland Conference play.
articles.headline: Lamar keeps Incarnate Word winless in Southland, 85-62

articles.description: James Harvey scored 17 points with four 3-pointers, Kalob Ledoux added 16 points with three 3s, and McNeese State held off Central Arkansas 76-72 on Wednesday night.
articles.headline: McNeese State holds off Central Arkansas 76-72

articles.description: Caleb Green scored 18 points and Holy Cross edged Army 70-65 on Wednesday night.
articles.headline: Green with 18 points leads Holy Cross over Army 70-65
